---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE_CONFIG } from '../config';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Us - InSpotGO"
  description="Learn about InSpotGO's mission, editorial approach, and the audience we serve — independent tech and SaaS reviews for English-speaking professionals."
>
  <div class="container content-page">

    <h1>About InSpotGO</h1>

    <div class="intro">
      <p class="lead">
        InSpotGO is an independent review site helping professionals and business owners discover the best tech products, software, and SaaS tools — through honest, benefit-focused content with no sponsored reviews.
      </p>
    </div>

    <section>
      <h2>Who We Are</h2>
      <p>
        InSpotGO was founded by <strong>César Muniz</strong>, a digital entrepreneur and web developer focused on helping English-speaking audiences navigate the increasingly crowded world of SaaS tools and technology products.
      </p>
      <p>
        The site operates as an independent editorial platform. We are not a marketing agency, a sponsored content hub, or a brand mouthpiece. Every review is produced with one goal: helping the reader make a better decision.
      </p>
      <p>
        You can connect with the founder on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/c%C3%A9sar-victor-de-souza-muniz-aa09a018b/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Our Audience</h2>
      <p>
        InSpotGO serves <strong>English-speaking professionals, freelancers, and small business owners</strong> — primarily in the US and global markets — who research software and SaaS tools before committing to a subscription or purchase.
      </p>
      <p>Our readers typically:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Are evaluating SaaS tools for business or personal productivity</li>
        <li>Want real-world benefit analysis, not a feature dump or a price table</li>
        <li>Are comparing 2–3 options and need clarity on which fits their workflow</li>
        <li>Trust independent editorial sources over vendor marketing pages</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Content is distributed organically through search (SEO-driven), with a focus on long-term evergreen rankings over viral short-term traffic.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>What We Cover</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>SaaS & Software Reviews</strong> — project management, productivity, CRM, marketing, and business tools</li>
        <li><strong>Tech Product Reviews</strong> — laptops, accessories, and professional-grade hardware</li>
        <li><strong>Comparison Guides</strong> — head-to-head breakdowns of competing tools with clear recommendations</li>
        <li><strong>Buying Guides</strong> — structured decision frameworks for readers choosing between multiple options</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Our Editorial Approach</h2>
      <p>
        InSpotGO publishes <strong>evergreen, benefit-focused content</strong>. We deliberately avoid writing about specific prices or promotional offers — because prices change, but a tool's core value does not.
      </p>
      <p>
        Every article is researched through primary sources, hands-on testing where possible, and analysis of real user feedback. Affiliate links are present in our content but never influence what we recommend or how we rate a product.
      </p>
      <p>For full details on our standards, see our <a href="/editorial-policy">Editorial Policy</a>.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Affiliate Disclosure</h2>
      <p>
        InSpotGO earns revenue through affiliate commissions. When you sign up for or purchase a product through our links, we may receive a commission — at no extra cost to you. This is how we sustain the site and keep all content free for readers.
      </p>
      <p>
        Affiliate relationships do not influence our editorial decisions. We only recommend tools we have independently evaluated and believe are genuinely useful. For complete details, see our <a href="/affiliate-disclosure">Affiliate Disclosure</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions, partnership inquiries, or feedback? We'd love to hear from you.
      </p>
      <p>
        📧 <a href="mailto:hello@inspotgo.com">hello@inspotgo.com</a>
      </p>
      <p>Or visit our <a href="/contact">Contact page</a>.</p>
    </section>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .content-page {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 3rem 1rem;
  }
  h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }
  .intro {
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }
  .lead {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-text-light);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: var(--color-bg-alt);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-primary);
    border-radius: 0 var(--radius-md) var(--radius-md) 0;
    margin: 0;
  }
  section {
    margin: 2.5rem 0;
    padding-bottom: 2.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }
  section:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }
  p {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-text-light);
  }
  ul {
    margin: 1rem 0;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }
  li {
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-light);
  }
  a {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    h1 { font-size: 2rem; }
  }
</style>
